Input:
    Dataset D with feature matrix X and user labels U
    Set of models M
    Number of splits S

For each split s in {1 ... S}:
    Stratified split D into training and test sets

    For each user u in U:
        Create binary labels:
            y = 1 if sample belongs to user u
            y = 0 otherwise

        For each model m in M:
            Train m on training data
            Compute decision scores on test data

            Compute:
                FAR
                FRR
                EER
                AUC

            Record metrics

Aggregate results across users and splits
Return mean and standard deviation of metrics
